title: For Sale:  WALTHER P99 AS .40 S&W
postcontent: This Walther P99 AS (Anti-Stress & Chambered in .40 S&W) comes closest to a traditional Double-Action/Single-Action trigger with a decocker. In Double-Action mode the internal striker is at rest with no pre-load and the trigger travel is 14 mm (0.55 in) long at approximately 38 N (8.5 lbf) trigger pull. When the slide is racked completely to the rear upon (re)loading, the internal striker is manually pre-cocked to Single-Action mode and the trigger remains in the forward position for the first shot and the Anti Stress mode is activated. The trigger travel is 14 mm (0.55 in) long in the Anti Stress mode at approximately 20 N (4.5 lbf) trigger pull. On all subsequent shots, the P99AS is automatically pre-cocked and the trigger travel is reduced to 8 mm (0.3 in) at the same 20 N (4.5 lbf) trigger pull. For manually deactivating the Anti Stress mode and setting the pistol to Double-Action mode the P99AS features a decock key or knob on the slide. The Anti Stress mode can also be manually activated by moving the slide approximately 10 mm (0.4 in) back. It has a Double-Sided mag release on the trigger guard. I am including 150 Jacketed Hollow Point and 150 Standard rounds, totalling 300 rounds, a Blackhawk holster, All factory paperwork, 4 mags, and a quick loader. I have also included a picture of the serial number for easy lookup. Please call David at REDACTED.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 4506-1 Stainless 45ACP - 5" IN BOX  3 MAGS
postcontent:
The Smith & Wesson 4506 is an all stainless steel 3rd generation semi-auto  pistol chambered in .45 ACP with an 8 round single stack magazine, 5" barrel, and Novak Lo-Mount 3 dot sights. Manufactured from 1989-1999, it found quick acceptance by law enforcement and remains one of the most iconic duty pistols of the 1990s as seen on TV in Miami Vice and Terminator movies to mention just a few. This is a big bad pistol with the legendary stopping power of the .45 cal. round. 
This pistol is a late model 4506-1 manufactured 6/11/1998. The Hogue grips are brand new and the finish is a very good @ 95%. The pistol is exceptionally clean and the internals were polished for butter smooth action including an awesome Performance Center quality trigger for oustanding accuracy. There are no noticeable signs of wear and the bore is excellent.It comes with three 8 round magazines in a Smith & Wesson plastic case including the original instruction manual.
The action is called Traditional Double Action (TDA) which describes a longer 1st shot trigger pull which cocks the hammer, and single action short, crisp, and light trigger pull on subsequent shots. The spurred hammer can be manually cocked to single action as well. An ambidextrous safety / decocker is featured for convenience and ultimate safety. These pistols were overbuilt to last a lifetime.  By today's standards this is no carry gun at 41 ozs., but an ideal collector piece or perfect for home protection and an absolute joy at the range. 
Please email  or call / text Bill 813 . 857 . 8287 for more info or pictures. I'm willing to meet anywhere in the bay area to show this fine pistol.
